The object of theology; theology and religious studies; theology and religions; mythological, metaphysical and christological theology; paradigms of Christian theology; the present source and task of theology; the disciplines of theology and the curricula in theology at the University of Tartu; religion and ethics; theology and the critique of religion; theology and other academic disciplines; theology, divine service and communication of faith. The perspective of religious studies, the position of the scholar, method, insider-outsider problem, main subdisciplines (comparative religion, anthropology of religion, psychology of religion, sociology of religion, philosophy of religion), other new approaches, the question of practical applicability. Course HVHV.00.017 Studies at the Faculty of Arts and Humanities is also part of this course.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Introduction to theology and religious studies.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After the completion of the course the student: 1)	discerns the basic ways of understanding and doing theology, as well as knows some considerations concerning their strengths and weaknesses; 2)	understands the goals, research perspectives and different approaches of religious studies; 3)	navigates in the disciplinary structure of theology and in its basic conceptual differentiations; 4)	is familiar with the different subdisciplines of religious studies, including their research methods and interrelatedness; 5)	is capable of discussing the relevance and role of theology in the contemporary pluralistic world, social co-existence and personal life;  6)	is capable of discussing and analysing the role and application of religious studies in the analysis of the contemporary world; 7)     see also the learning outcomes of the course HVHV.00.017 Studies at the Faculty of Arts and Humanities.
